{
  "$comment": "Single source of truth for the cross-platform TV screen gallery. Each scenario maps one canonical key to how every platform renders that state: `web` drives capture-web.mjs (display test harness URL params), `tvos` drives capture-tvos.sh (HEXSHOT/HEXPLAYERS env, mirrored by appletv/UITests/ScreenshotTests.swift), `android` names the Roborazzi PNG emitted by the :tv screenshot tests (collect-shots.mjs renames it to the canonical key). The DATA behind every row comes from server/GalleryFixtures.js (shipped in dist/partycore.js), so all three columns render identical rosters/boards/results; `variant` names a GalleryFixtures board variant. A platform without an entry has no equivalent for that state (e.g. focus states on non-TV web); gen-gallery.mjs renders that as an explicit gap.",
